                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00 Statement July 16, 1937/87: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Owsley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-05T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 5, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 5—10:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Department’s circular telegram August 4, 1 p.m.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The Danish Government share the view that hostilities in any one part of the
                        world exercise their influence everywhere.</p>
                    <p>We join in the desire for the preservation of peace expressed by Secretary of
                        State Cordell Hull; it is also our desire that all states will refrain from
                        the use of power against others and desist from <pb facs="0765" n="753"
                            xml:id="pg_753"/> interference in the internal affairs of other states.
                        We share the hope for the strengthening of international law and for the
                        recovery of economic stability all over the world just as we adhere to the
                        desire for a limitation and reduction of armaments. We express the hope that
                        the participation of the United States of America in the efforts to carry
                        these ideas into practice will lead to the desired end.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Please see my despatch No. 8,<note n="88" xml:id="d771fn88">Not printed.</note>
                    mailed registered July 31.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Owsley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
